item.dc:creator: @imsokool22 imsokool22
item.description:
@imsokool22 wrote:

yes. you only need to open up port 43594.for utorrent portforwarding:
1.start your server
2.press ctrl and p
3.click Connections
4.Type 43594 in the box next to random port
5.click apply then ok then do step 2 again
6.now click random port then click apply then ok and now cancel utorrent down(red X) then go to system try(where volume is) and
(click the < if u dont see utorrent symbol) then right click the symbol and click cancel if you followed this correctly you have added an exception to your windows firewall.If it didnt work then try the 1 in the tutorial section(cant portforward? Try the easy way or w\e it says)
